Join the Conversation To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs Dez after loss: Cowboys will still 'run the East' Mike Leslie and Landon Haaf, WFAA Sports 7:29 p.m. CDT October 25, 2015 Dez Bryant walking off the field after the game Sunday at MetLife Stadium (Photo: Mike Leslie, WFAA) CONNECT 10 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Dez Bryant still hasn't lost faith in his team after a fourth straight loss with him on the sidelines. 
The Matt Cassel Experience was a everything short of a tremendous letdown, aside from one fantastic throw for the game-tying touchdown in the fourth quarter. The veteran replacement for Brandon Weeden completed 20 of his 27 passes -- except three were completed to members of the Giants secondary. 
Even still, Bryant walked off the field with some swagger. 
The star wideout, who hasn't played since Week 1 due to a broken bone in his foot, told hecklers in the stands at MetLife Stadium that the Cowboys would still "run the [NFC] East," pointing to the star on his chest. #Cowboys @DezBryant leaves the field with a promise - "We still gon' run the East!"

 #WFAACowboys #NFL pic.twitter.com/5u5gyo2IiT â€” Mike Leslie (@MikeLeslieWFAA) October 25, 2015 
WFAA's Mike Leslie captured the moment on video . 
Dallas is 1.5 games behind the division-leading Giants after breaking a seven-game road winning streak against NFC East rivals. An anemic passing attack has hindered the Cowboys without Bryant and starting quarterback Tony Romo. Darren McFadden put up 152 rushing yards in Sunday's loss.
